			<slide id="digital-transformation-definition">
				<title>Digital Transformation Definition</title>
				<img src="services-cycle.png" title="Digital Transformation Pillars" style="float: right ; width : 30% ; margin : 0% 5% 5% 5% ; "/>
				<p style="padding : 2em ;">Digital Transformation <a href="https://hbr.org/2019/07/digital-doesnt-have-to-be-disruptive"><q>means adapting an organization's strategy and structure to capture opportunities enabled by digital technology.</q> <span style="font-size : 75% ;">(Nathan Furr and Andrew Shipilov, <q>Digital Doesn't Have to Be Disruptive</q>, Harvard Business Review 97(4), July/August 2019, pp. 94-103)</span></a></p>
			</slide>
			<slide id="digital-transformation-tech">
				<title>Digital Transformation: Business &amp; Technology Align</title>
				<img href="https://medium.com/featured-insights/the-path-to-devops-ec47dca758a0" title='Erik Dörnenburg, "The Path to DevOps", ThoughtWorks Featured Insights, February 2019' src="devops-path.png" style=" width : 90% ; height : 70% ; object-fit : contain ; margin : 0% 4% 0% 4% ; "/>
			</slide>
			<slide id="api-unicorn">
				<title>APIs Fix Anything!</title>
				<img src="hype-cycle-unicorn.png" style=" width : 90% ; height : 70% ; object-fit : contain ; margin : 0% 4% 0% 4% ; "/>
			</slide>
			<slide id="api-plumbing">
				<title>APIs Are Just Plumbing</title>
				<img src="hype-cycle-unicorn-plumbing.png" style=" width : 90% ; height : 70% ; object-fit : contain ; margin : 0% 4% 0% 4% ; "/>
			</slide>
			<slide id="continuous-transformation">
				<title>Digital Transformation is Continuous</title>
				<ul>
					<li>Digital transformation happens at two different levels</li>
					<ul>
						<li>Transforming the organization to become better at adapting to changes</li>
						<li>Identifying and implementing capabilities that improve the organization</li>
					</ul>
					<li>You're never <q>done</q> with digital transformation</li>
					<ul>
						<li><em>Business</em> must be empowered and capable to identify opportunities</li>
						<li><em>Organization</em> must be capable of acting fast to capture opportunities</li> 
						<li><em>Technology</em> must be able to realize opportunities quickly and safely</li>
					</ul>
				</ul>
			</slide>
		</part>
		<part id="accelerate">
			<title>Accelerate</title>
			<slide id="success">
				<title>Outcomes over Output</title>
				<ul>
					<li>High failure rate of <q>digital transformation initiatives</q></li>
					<li>Technology is necessary but not sufficient</li>
					<ul>
						<li>It is important to <em>do things right</em></li>
						<li>It is even more important to <em>do the right things</em></li>
					</ul>
					<li>Help customers to make good decisions on three levels</li>
					<ul>
						<li>How to design, build, and manage individual <em>API products</em></li>
						<li>How to cultivate and evolve the <em>API landscape</em></li>
						<li>How to align overall strategy towards API success</li>
					</ul>
				</ul>
			</slide>
